##

EXAMPLE: tests/expression_continuation.stult

This example checks expression line-continuation syntax.

A trailing binary operator continues an expression onto the next line. The same
rule applies to arithmetic, comparison, equality and logical operators.

A trailing conditional-expression branch separator also continues onto the next
line.

##

ASSERT : STD.ERROR.ASSERT

total : 1 +
	2 *
	3 -
	4 /
	2

ASSERT.EQUAL(total, 5, "trailing arithmetic operators should continue expressions")

is_total_five : total =
	5

ASSERT.TRUE(is_total_five, "trailing equality operators should continue expressions")

allowed : (
	total >= 5 &
	total <= 5 |
	total > 100
)

ASSERT.TRUE(allowed, "trailing logical operators should continue grouped expressions")

label : (allowed) : (
	"allowed" |
	"blocked"
)

ASSERT.EQUAL(label, "allowed", "trailing branch separators should continue conditional expressions")
